{"id":"project-LICHEN-shnr","title":"SLIP transport: slip_iface_send doesn't validate IPv6 packet","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/slip_transport.c
Lines: 439-496

slip_iface_send() is the network interface callback for sending packets. Unlike slip_dispatch_packet() which calls validate_ipv6_packet() on received packets, the send path doesn't validate the packet:

    static int slip_iface_send(const struct device *dev, struct net_pkt *pkt)
    {
        ...
        if (pkt_len > sizeof(pkt_buf)) {
            LOG_WRN("SLIP TX: packet too large");
            ...
        }
        // No IPv6 validation!
        ...
        ret = slip_encode(pkt_buf, pkt_len, ctx->tx_frame, ...);
        ...
    }

While Zephyr's network stack should only send valid IPv6 packets, a bug elsewhere could result in:
1. Non-IPv6 data being sent (ethernet frames, raw data)
2. Malformed IPv6 packets (wrong version, truncated headers)
3. Packets that claim to be larger than they are

The direct API slip_transport_send() also lacks validation.

Fix: Add validate_ipv6_packet() call in the TX path, or document that validation is the caller's responsibility.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:55:41.711588Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:55:41.711617Z"}

